[2] The Americas
Date: Wed 2 Feb 2011
Source: PAHO Epidemiological Alert: Update on Dengue Situation in the
Americas [summarized, edited]
<http://new.paho.org/hq/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=5013&Itemid=2206>


- Bolivia.
Distribution: highest incidence in 3 of 9 departments [state or
province equivalent]: Beni, Santa Cruz and Cochabamba.
Cases: Up to epidemiological week (EW) 4, 1988 cases with 5.8 percent
confirmed; 8 deaths with suspected severe dengue, all in Beni.
Dengue virus serotypes circulating: 1, 2 and 3

- Peru.
Distribution and cases: from EW 51 2010 - EW 3 2011, 533 cases
reported, with 209 serious and 13 fatal and confirmed.
Dengue virus serotypes circulating: 1, 2, 3, and 4.

- The Americas.
[See URL above for a map showing dengue incidence in the Americas in
2010. - Mod.TY]

