[4] Cases in various countries: Bolivia (Amazon region), Paraguay
(eastern), Brazil (Rio de Janeiro state), Brazil (Ceara), Brazil
(Parana), Australia (north Queensland)

- Bolivia (Amazon region). Tue 1 Feb 2011. The Minister of Health
reported that since October (2010) to date (1 Feb 2011), there have
been 9 dengue deaths and 1470 confirmed dengue cases, most of which
have occurred in Trinidad, Santa Ana del Yacuma and San Borja.
<http://www.laprensa.com.bo/noticias/1-2-2011/noticias/01-02-2011_10606.php>

- Paraguay (eastern). 9 Feb 2011. The municipal government of the
Ciudad del Este, in the eastern area of Parana department along the
border with Brazil, this Friday (6 Feb 2011) issued a health alert in
the region because a dengue outbreak has caused the deaths of at
least 4 people, with another 163 ill from the virus infection in the
area. As of today (6 Feb 2011), the national system of health
surveillance reported that up to epidemiological week 4 (the 5th week
of the year), 895 suspected dengue cases are reported, of which 163
have been confirmed.
<http://www.telesurtv.net/secciones/noticias/88475-NN/declaran-alerta-sanitaria-por-brote-de-dengue-al-este-de-paraguay/>

[A map showing the location of Parana department and the Ciudad el
Este can be accessed at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/paraguay_pol98.jpg>.
A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Paraguay can be accessed
at <http://healthmap.org/promed/index.php?v=-23.2,-58.4,5>. - Mod.TY]

- Brazil (Rio de Janeiro state). 6 Feb 2011. Although reported dengue
cases nationally are 56 per cent fewer than those reported last year
(2010), according to official data, Rio de Janeiro and another 18
neighboring municipalities are on alert, with 633 cases in the 1st
month of the year (2011), an increase of 597 per cent compared to
January of 2010.
<http://www.ansa.it/ansalatina/notizie/notiziari/brasil/20110206203135214999.html>

[A map showing the states of Brazil can be accessed at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/brazil.jpg>. A
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Brazil can be accessed at
<http://healthmap.org/promed/index.php?v=-10.8,-53.1,4>. - Mod.TY]

- Brazil (Ceara). 5 Feb 2011. Ceara state registered its 1st fatal
dengue case in Itaitinga. Fortaleza now has counted 428 cases of the
disease. Up to the present in Ceara, 2567 suspected dengue cases have
been identified in 106 municipalities. Of these, 1352 were confirmed
in 78 cities, with 9 cases of DHF.
<http://diariodonordeste.globo.com/materia.asp?codigo=928948>

- Brazil (Parana). 1 Feb 2011. Just this year (2011), there are 144
confirmed dengue cases in Londrina, 124 of which were locally
acquired within the city and 2 from outside. According to a bulletin
issued by the state Secretariat of Health, as of yesterday (31 Jan
2011), there have been 390 confirmed dengue cases in Parana, with 375
locally acquired and 15 imported, as well as an additional 3484
suspected dengue cases in the state.
<http://www.jornalfloripa.com.br/brasil/ver_info_jornalfloripa.asp?NewsID=10317>

- Australia (north Queensland). 8 Feb 2011. Authorities in Innisfail,
south of Cairns in far north Queensland, are continuing to warn
people about the threat of dengue fever, with 7 cases now confirmed.
There have also been 2 new cases of dengue fever diagnosed in the
Townsville suburb of Cranbrook.
<http://au.news.yahoo.com/a/-/australian-news/8797230/more-dengue-cases-trigger-health-warning/>

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map showing Queensland state in
northeastern Australia can be accessed at
<http://healthmap.org/promed/index.php?v=-25.7,134.5,4>. - Mod.TY]

